comment: Towns (MIN) makes incidental contact with Booker (PHO) as he attempts to go around the screen.
Towns (MIN) continues moving as he sets the screen on Knight (PHO) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Wiggins (MIN) legally contests Knight's (PHO) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Chandler (PHO) makes incidental contact with Towns (MIN) that does not dislodge him or affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
RATR shows that LaVine (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and Rubio (MIN) cleanly strips the ball from Booker (PHO) on the drive to the basket.
Booker (PHO) makes contact with Rubio (MIN) that affects his RSBQ.
Towns (MIN) and Len (PHO) briefly engage and separate during the inbounds play.
LaVine (MIN) makes contact with Booker's (PHO) arms on his driving shot attempt. Booker has already gathered the ball when the contact occurs and continuation is correctly awarded.
Len (PHO) makes incidental contact with Wiggins (MIN) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Len (PHO) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) head on his driving shot attempt.
Len (PHO) sets the screen on Wiggins (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
